#: ../../L/low-bandwidth.rst:9
msgid ""
"[from communication theory] Used to indicate a talk that, although not "
":ref:`content-free`\\, was not terribly informative. \"That was a low-"
"bandwidth talk, but what can you expect for an audience of :ref:`suit`\\s!\""
" Compare :ref:`zero-content`\\, :ref:`bandwidth`\\, :ref:`math-out`\\."
msgstr ""
"[通信理論から] \\ :ref:`content-free`\\ ではないにせよ、さほど情報量の多くなかった話を示すのに使われる。「あれはlow-"
"bandwidthな話だったが、\\ :ref:`suit`\\ の聴衆に何を期待できようか!」\\ :ref:`zero-content`\\ 、\\"
" :ref:`bandwidth`\\ 、\\ :ref:`math-out`\\ と比較せよ。"
